The paper deals with game theory and optimization problems in the context of bandwidth allocation, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.GT" (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely category, as the paper explicitly mentions the existence and properties of Nash equilibria. "cs.NE" (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category, given the focus on bandwidth allocation. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) and "cs.IT" (Information Theory) are possible categories, as the paper discusses computational complexity and convergence properties of algorithms. "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category, as the paper deals with resource allocation in a networked setting.
